# reposix — environment variables template.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` at the repo root and fill in the values. The
# real `.env` is gitignored; `.env.example` is committed so contributors
# discover which variables exist.
#
# Loading: no in-process dotenv loader. Source the file before running
# reposix commands that need the variables (this is also what makes the
# `$VAR` references and `$(...)` expansions in `.env` resolve):
#
#   set -a; source .env; set +a
#   reposix list --backend confluence --project YOUR_SPACE_KEY
#
# Or pass them inline:
#
#   ATLASSIAN_API_KEY=xxx ATLASSIAN_EMAIL=you@example.com \
#     REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_TENANT=yourtenant \
#     reposix list --backend confluence --project YOUR_SPACE_KEY
#
# ------------------------------------------------ CI secrets (GitHub Actions)
# The canonical repo (reubenjohn/reposix) mirrors these as GitHub Actions
# secrets (write-only; `gh secret list -R reubenjohn/reposix` shows names).
# Recorded here so future maintainers know what CI expects provisioned:
#     Set as Actions secrets:  ATLASSIAN_API_KEY  ATLASSIAN_EMAIL
#       REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_TENANT  REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_SPACE  JIRA_EMAIL
#       JIRA_API_TOKEN  REPOSIX_JIRA_INSTANCE  CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN
#     Auto-injected by Actions, never set manually:  GITHUB_TOKEN
#     CI-only, not needed for local dev:  CODECOV_TOKEN  HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN
#     Not yet on CI (gap):  JIRA_TEST_PROJECT — real-backend JIRA tests default
#       the project key to `TEST`; set this to your live key (the owner's is
#       `KAN`) and forward it in ci.yml's integration-contract-jira-v09 job.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------- GitHub
# Optional. Lifts GithubReadOnlyBackend's anonymous 60 req/hr limit to
# 1000 req/hr (or 5000 with a PAT). In dev, reuse the token the gh CLI
# already manages (auto-rotates; nothing secret stored in the file):
#   GITHUB_TOKEN=$(gh auth token 2>/dev/null || true)
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# --------------------------------------------------------------- Atlassian
# Atlassian Cloud credentials — shared by BOTH Confluence and JIRA (one
# account, one API token). Used by reposix-confluence + reposix-jira via
# REST Basic auth.
#
# ATLASSIAN_API_KEY: API token issued from
#   https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
#   ACCOUNT-SCOPED: it only works with the email the account is registered
#   under (see ATLASSIAN_EMAIL).
# ATLASSIAN_EMAIL:   the account email shown at top-right on that page.
#                    Must match the token's issuing account EXACTLY.
ATLASSIAN_API_KEY=
ATLASSIAN_EMAIL=

# -------------------------------------------------------------- Confluence
# REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_TENANT: subdomain of your Atlassian Cloud tenant
#   (e.g. `mycompany` for https://mycompany.atlassian.net).
# REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_SPACE:  the space key to browse (e.g. `TokenWorld`).
REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_TENANT=
REPOSIX_CONFLUENCE_SPACE=

# --------------------------------------------------------------------- JIRA
# Same Atlassian credential as above, under JIRA-specific names — the code
# has NO ATLASSIAN_* fallback, so these must be set even though the values
# are identical. When shell-sourcing you can reference the Atlassian vars:
#   JIRA_EMAIL=$ATLASSIAN_EMAIL
#   JIRA_API_TOKEN=$ATLASSIAN_API_KEY
#
# REPOSIX_JIRA_INSTANCE: BARE subdomain, e.g. `mycompany` (the adapter appends
#   `.atlassian.net`). scripts/preflight-real-backends.sh mirrors the adapter:
#   bare subdomain preferred; a value containing a dot is used as a full host.
# JIRA_TEST_PROJECT: project key for real-backend tests. Resolution precedence
#   is JIRA_TEST_PROJECT > REPOSIX_JIRA_PROJECT > default `TEST`.
JIRA_EMAIL=
JIRA_API_TOKEN=
REPOSIX_JIRA_INSTANCE=
JIRA_TEST_PROJECT=

# -------------------------------------------------------------- Allowlist
# reposix-core's SG-01 egress allowlist. Default is loopback-only. When
# using the GitHub / Confluence / JIRA backends, MUST be widened to include
# the real API origin(s). Comma-separated globs; only `*` on port supported.
#
# Example for dev against all real backends:
# REPOSIX_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://127.0.0.1:*,http://localhost:*,https://api.github.com,https://<tenant>.atlassian.net
REPOSIX_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://127.0.0.1:*,http://localhost:*

# ------------------------------------------------------------ crates.io
# release-plz publish token (CI secret: CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN). Not needed for
# local dev unless you publish crates. Scopes: publish-new, publish-update, yank.
CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN=
